# Trivy vulnerability allowlist  —  IRT-1390
#
# Scope of this file:
#  - CI GATE (.github/workflows/build-images.yml) scans OS/base packages only
#    (trivy --ignore-unfixed --pkg-types os) and reads this file, so an OS CVE listed here is
#    accepted and won't fail the gate.
#  - CI SARIF upload sets TRIVY_IGNOREFILE=/dev/null, so the Security > Code scanning report shows
#    EVERYTHING regardless of this file — full visibility is intentional (even accepted findings stay
#    on the dashboard as an audit trail).
#  - Local/manual `trivy image <img>` runs (README "Scan locally") read this file by default, so
#    entries here also keep those scans clean.
#
# OS/base CVEs: add one to silence the gate when a finding is a false positive, unreachable in our
# config, or awaiting a Rocky/DHI erratum.
#
# Library / application-JAR CVEs come from the BridgeLink Core release tarball and are NOT gated here
# (the gate is OS-only); they are tracked in IRT-1396. Add one only after Core has assessed it as
# not-exploitable / unfixable, so local library scans (trivy image --pkg-types library) are clean;
# it still shows on the CI Security tab.
#
# Format: justification + review date on the comment line(s) ABOVE the bare CVE ID (portable across
# Trivy versions). Keep the list short; re-review dated entries.

# CVE-2022-46337 (Apache Derby, embedded-only) — accepted per IRT-1396 triage. Not exploitable:
# BridgeLink uses Derby strictly embedded (EmbeddedDriver, local jdbc:derby: appdata paths) with no
# network server and no Derby authentication configured, so the LDAP-authenticator vector does not
# exist. No Java-17 binary fix is published (10.16.1.2 was never released to Maven Central; 10.17
# requires Java 21). Revisit when the platform moves to Java 21.
CVE-2022-46337
